We have been having a perplexing issue with our Wolverine gamepads. The right thumbstick occasionally swaps x and y axis, and the triggers will swap from going zero to positive one, zero to negative one.

In one case it lasted for a day. In another it fixed after a plug/unplug/plug cycle. Both our gamepads have done this.

It never happened last year, even once.

Has something changed in the driver station that would cause this? We do not run the razor synapse software, these are not map-able buttons, and the controller is recognized as an xbox controller.

See

CommandXboxController / leftTrigger() and rightTrigger() not triggering Java
Hello Somehow the leftTrigger() and rightTrigger() from CommandXboxController are not triggering when used with our trusted Xbox 360 controller (and same for axisGreaterThan/axisSmallerThan when used against the triggers). All the other buttons do work, as well as axisGreaterThan/axisSmallerThan when used against the left and right sticks of the controller. Anyone else observing this issue? Thanks.

Try upgrading to DS 23.1 (latest Game Tools release), it’s been reported to fix this.
